    "body": "Problem:  Hidden windows are redrawn unnecessarily.\r\nSolution: If a window is hidden, don't bother drawing it.",
    "closed_at": "2026-06-02T12:51:09Z",
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "_links": {
                "html": {
                    "href": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/40057#discussion_r3329513779"
                },
                "pull_request": {
                    "href": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/pulls/40057"
                },
                "self": {
                    "href": "https://api.github.com/repos/neovim/neovim/pulls/comments/3329513779"
                }
            },
            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "maybe an exception should be made for the global stl? if a hidden win is current, then the global stl won't be drawn anymore (missing after `mode`)\r\n\r\n```vim\r\nset ls=3\r\ncall nvim_open_win(0,1,#{relative:'editor',width:5,height:5,row:0,col:0,hide:1})\r\nmode\r\n```\r\n\r\nalso `hide` can currently be set for splits (for better or for worse 😇), which will cause such splits to be redrawn without a stl:\r\n\r\n```vim\r\nto sp\r\ncall nvim_win_set_config(0,#{hide:1})\r\nmode\r\n```\r\n\r\n(i suppose that one's really an issue with how `hide`'s validated :melting_face:)",
            "commit_id": "b706c835dd4ba27985411863a8d767168887b75b",
            "created_at": "2026-05-31T00:29:51Z",
            "diff_hunk": "@@ -232,6 +231,10 @@ static void win_redr_custom(win_T *wp, bool draw_winbar, bool draw_ruler, bool u\n \n   ScreenGrid *grid = wp && wp->w_floating && !is_stl_global ? &wp->w_grid_alloc : &default_grid;\n \n+  if (wp != NULL && wp->w_config.hide) {\n+    return;  // unnecessary\n+  }",
            "html_url": "https://github.com/neovim/neovim/pull/40057#discussion_r3329513779",
